1180	虽然	雖然	suīrán	although / even though	conjunction	关联词	Correlative	虚词	Function Words	\N	\N	\N	sui1ran2.mp3	This conjunction is often used as a connecting word in the main clause of subordinate complex sentences. 4559	无论	無論	wúlùn	no matter what / regardless of whether	conjunction	关联词	Correlative	虚词	Function Words	\N	\N	\N	wu2lun4.mp3	This conjunction is often used as a connecting word in the subordinate clause of subordinate complex sentences. It is often used in the pattern 无论…，都… to express that even if different conditions exist still there is something that remains the same.  See <a href='http://chinesenotes.com/grammar_complex.php#subordinate'>Subordinate Complex Sentences</a>.

4632	呢	\N	ne	question particle for subjects already mentioned	particle	语气助词	Modal Particle	虚词	Function Words	\N	\N	\N	ne.mp3	1. 呢 can be placed at the end of an affirmative / negative question to indicate uncertainty. 2. 呢 can be placed at the tail of a sentence with an interrogative pronoun to indicate conjecture. 3. 呢 can be used in a question with an alternative to indicate a tone of interrogation. 4. 呢 can be appended to a noun or pronoun to ask a one-member question. 5. 呢 can be used at the end of a declaritive sentence to indicate that an action or condition is still continuing.

10750	既然	\N	jìrán	since / as / this being the case	conjunction	关联词	Correlative	虚词	Function Words	\N	\N	\N	\N	This conjunction is often used as a connecting word in the subordinate clause of subordinate complex sentences.  It is often used in the pattern 既然…，就… to express a conclusion deduced from a premise.  See <a href='http://chinesenotes.com/grammar_complex.php#subordinate'>Subordinate Complex Sentences</a>.

11131	一	\N	yī	as soon as / throughout	adverb	关联词	Correlative	特点	Characteristic	\N	\N	\N	yi1.mp3	This adverb is often used as a connecting word in the subordinate clause of subordinate complex sentences. It is often used in the pattern 一…，就… to express that if a certain condition is met the result will surely follow. See <a href='http://chinesenotes.com/grammar_complex.php#subordinate'>Subordinate Complex Sentences</a>.

11134	一边	一邊	yībiān	on the one hand / on the other hand / doing while	adverb	关联词	Correlative	虚词	Function Words	\N	\N	\N	\N	The form 一边…一边… is usually used to indicate that two actions are occuring at the same time.  It is often used in coordinate complex sentences. See <a href='http://chinesenotes.com/grammar_complex.php#coordinate'>Coordinate Complex Sentences</a>.  When the following verb is monosyllabic 一边 can be abbreviated to 边.

20916	一方面	\N	yīfāngmiàn	on the one hand / on the other hand	adverb	关联词	Correlative	虚词	Function Words	\N	\N	\N	\N	The form 一方面…一方面… is usually used to indicate that two conditions coexist.  It is often used in coordinate complex sentences. See <a href='http://chinesenotes.com/grammar_complex.php#coordinate'>Coordinate Complex Sentences</a>.  It is most often used for abstract conditions.

21011	十地	\N	shí dì	the ten grounds of the bodhisattva path / Dashabhumi	proper noun	\N	\N	佛教	Buddhism	\N	\N	\N	\N	The ten stages of bodhisattva development into a Buddha.  The ten grounds are: (1) the ground of joy 欢喜地; (2) the ground of freedom from defilement 离垢地; (3) the ground of radiance 发光地; (4) the ground of brilliant wisdom 燄慧地; (5) the ground of mastery of final difficulties 难胜地; (6) the ground of manifesting prajna-wisdom 现前地; (7) the ground of proceeding afar 远行地; (8) the ground of attaining calm 不动地; (9) the ground of finest discriminatory wisdom 善慧地; (10) the ground of Dharma cloud 法云地.
